widest points, while the planet itself is over 12,000 kilometers in diameter.""Meaning, even that is just 0.0008% the size of Earth."SOURCES: NASA, Popular Mechanics, Popular Science, Quartz https://www.nasa.gov/mission_pages/station/news/orbital_debris.htmlhttps://www.popularmechanics.com/space/satellites/g2951/7-of-the-biggest-things-put-in-space/https://www.popsci.com/space-junk-why-cant-we-see-satellites-in-images-earthhttps://qz.com/458826/behold-nasas-first-image-in-decades-of-the-whole-earth/***]]></description>
