      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANFans attending the 2018 World Cup in Russia will need a "Fan ID" in addition to standard match tickets.According to information from the Fan ID and FIFA websites, the document can only be got after buying official tickets from FIFA, then by applying for the document at a seperate website or at a distribution center in Russia. Successful applicants, are notified by email or text and the ID is sent by mail, or collected from a center.The document allows visa-free entry to Russia for 10 days prior to the document holder's first match and 10 days after their last match. Fan ID and ticket holders will also be able to travel between cities for free using trains and other public transport.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Depiction of fan presenting Fan ID and ticket at world cup match2. Depiction of how fan ID is got3. Depiction of visa-free travel and duration of stay4. Depiction of transportation between Russian citiesVOICEOVER (in English): "To enter stadiums during the 2018 World Cup in Russia, fans will need to present a 'Fan ID' in addition to their normal ticket.""Reportedly, these are designed to nullify touting and for security purposes.""Fan IDs can only be acquired after buying official tickets from FIFA, then by applying for the ID at a seperate website or at a distribution center in Russia.""Successful applicants are notified by email or text, and the ID is sent by mail, or collected from a center."  "The document allows visa-free entry to Russia for 10 days prior to the document's first match and 10 days after their last match.""Fan ID and ticket holders will also be able to travel between cities for free using trains and other public transport."SOURCES: FIFA, Fan-ID, ESPNhttp://www.fifa.com/worldcup/organisation/fan-id/index.htmlhttps://www.fan-id.ruhttp://global.espn.com/football/world-cup-soccer/4/blog/post/3408421/world-cup-100-days-out-russia-face-challenges-like-racism-fan-safety-and-price-gouging***]]></description>
