ted.""The odds of getting sick are highest among the 11 passengers seated closest to the sick person  three beside, four in front, and four behind."SOURCES: Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of Americahttp://www.pnas.org/content/early/2018/03/13/1711611115http://www.afr.com/lifestyle/travel/world/to-avoid-germs-on-a-plane-consider-booking-a-window-seat-20180321-h0xt06***]]></description>
